title: 'Friends' star Courteney Cox didn't think Hollywood success was 'possibility' growing up in Alabama
description: Courteney Cox received a star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame where "Friends" co-stars Jennifer Aniston and Lisa Kudrow shared speeches on her behalf. Coco Arquette and Johnny McDaid also attended.

title: Ex-NFL running back Zac Stacy sentenced to jail time, probation after attacks on ex-girlfriend: report
description: Former NFL running back Zac Stacy will be serving six months in jail followed by one year of probation after pleading guilty to charges related to attacks on his ex-girlfriend.

title: Brandon Miller’s Twitter account disappears following backlash from controversial pregame ritual
description: Alabama's Brandon Miller seemingly deleted his Twitter account on Monday after facing backlash for his controversial pregame intro over the weekend.

title: US Marshals Service attacked by ransomware targeting sensitive law enforcement information: report
description: The U.S. Marshals Service was attacked by ransomware on Feb. 17, which targeted sensitive information and information about fugitives and investigations.

title: Thousands of Texas of Asian descent victims of driver’s license breach by criminal Chinese gang
description: The driver's licenses of thousands of Texas were shipped to a New York criminal gang, officials said Monday

title: Wisconsin Gov. Evers wants bars open until 4 a.m. at 2024 RNC
description: Democratic Wisconsin Gov. Tony Evers is pushing the state Legislature to allow bars in 14 counties surrounding Milwaukee to be open later during the 2024 Republican National Convention.

title: White House still backs gain-of-function research to prevent future pandemics: Kirby
description: National Security spokesman John Kirby says President Biden supports gain-of-function research conducted safely and securely and prevents future pandemics.

title: Serbia, Kosovo back EU diplomacy plan
description: The leaders of Serbia and Kosovo, Aleksandar Vucic and Albin Kurti, implicitly agreed to a European Union-sponsored plan to ease tensions between the two nations.
